{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NCPGuERepRaPpb1QP4kebe","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 3.3: Agent Resolver Module\n2\t\n3\tStatus: review\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want an agent-resolver that resolves configs through the embedded -> user -> project patch chain and compiles the result into a Claude Code inline subagent definition,\n11\tso that customizations overlay cleanly on embedded defaults and agents are ready for SDK dispatch.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** an embedded agent name like `\"dev\"` and no user or project patches\n16\t   **When** `resolveAgent(\"dev\")` is called\n17\t   **Then** the embedded config from `templates/agents/dev.yaml` is loaded, parsed, validated against `agent.schema.json`, and returned as a `ResolvedAgent` object\n18\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n19\t\n20\t2. **Given** an embedded agent `\"dev\"` and a user-level patch file at `~/.codeharness/agents/dev.patch.yaml` with `extends: embedded://dev` and `overrides:` that adds `personality.traits.rigor: 0.9`\n21\t   **When** `resolveAgent(\"dev\")` is called\n22\t   **Then** the embedded config is loaded first, the user patch overrides are deep-merged on top, and the resolved config includes both the original embedded fields and the new `personality.traits.rigor: 0.9`\n23\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t3. **Given** an embedded agent `\"dev\"`, a user-level patch, and a project-level patch at `.codeharness/agents/dev.patch.yaml` with `extends: embedded://dev` and `prompt_patches.append` text\n26\t   **When** `resolveAgent(\"dev\")` is called\n27\t   **Then** resolution order is: embedded base -> user patch merged -> project patch merged on top, and the final config includes the `prompt_patches.append` content in a `prompt_patches` field accessible for downstream compilation\n28\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n29\t\n30\t4. **Given** an embedded agent `\"dev\"` and no patch files exist at user or project level\n31\t   **When** `resolveAgent(\"dev\")` is called\n32\t   **Then** the missing patches are silently skipped (no error, no warning) and the embedded config is returned unchanged\n33\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t5. **Given** a patch file that contains invalid YAML syntax or fails schema validation after merge\n36\t   **When** `resolveAgent()` processes it\n37\t   **Then** a descriptive `AgentResolveError` is thrown with the file path, parse error or validation errors, and the specific problem ŌĆö resolution does NOT silently return a bad config\n38\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n39\t\n40\t6. **Given** a resolved agent config (after patch chain)\n41\t   **When** `compileSubagentDefinition()` is called\n42\t   **Then** it returns an object with `name` (string), `model` (string, defaulted), `instructions` (string compiled from persona.identity + communication_style + principles + prompt_patches.append), `disallowedTools` (array, from config or empty), and `bare: true`\n43\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n44\t\n45\t7. **Given** the evaluator agent with `disallowedTools: [\"Edit\", \"Write\"]`\n46\t   **When** compiled to a subagent definition\n47\t   **Then** the `disallowedTools` array is preserved in the compiled output\n48\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n49\t\n50\t8. **Given** a user creates a fully custom agent file (not a patch) at `.codeharness/agents/my-agent.yaml` with all required fields and no `extends:`\n51\t   **When** `resolveAgent(\"my-agent\")` is called\n52\t   **Then** the custom agent is loaded directly, validated against `agent.schema.json`, and returned without attempting to find an embedded base ŌĆö no patch chain applies\n53\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n54\t\n55\t9. **Given** `resolveAgent()` is called for all 9 embedded agents sequentially\n56\t   **When** timed\n57\t   **Then** total resolution completes in <200ms (NFR2)\n58\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n59\t\n60\t10. **Given** unit tests for the agent-resolver module\n61\t    **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n62\t    **Then** tests pass at 80%+ coverage for `src/lib/agent-resolver.ts` covering: embedded load, user patch merge, project patch merge, full 3-layer chain, missing patches skipped, malformed patch errors, subagent compilation with and without disallowedTools, custom agent (no extends), prompt_patches append, and no regressions in existing tests\n63\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n64\t\n65\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n66\t\n67\t- [x] Task 1: Define TypeScript interfaces (AC: #1, #6)\n68\t  - [ ] Define `ResolvedAgent` interface matching the agent schema shape plus optional `prompt_patches` field\n69\t  - [ ] Define `SubagentDefinition` interface with `name`, `model`, `instructions`, `disallowedTools`, `bare`\n70\t  - [ ] Define `AgentResolveError` error class with `filePath` and `errors` properties\n71\t  - [ ] Define `AgentPatch` interface for patch file structure: `extends`, `overrides`, `prompt_patches`\n72\t\n73\t- [x] Task 2: Implement embedded agent loading (AC: #1, #4)\n74\t  - [ ] Create `src/lib/agent-resolver.ts`\n75\t  - [ ] Implement `loadEmbeddedAgent(name: string)`: read from `templates/agents/{name}.yaml`, parse YAML, validate against agent schema, return typed config\n76\t  - [ ] Throw `AgentResolveError` if embedded agent file not found (fatal per architecture error handling)\n77\t  - [ ] Use `path.resolve(__dirname, '../../templates/agents/')` to locate embedded templates (same pattern as story 3-2 tests)\n78\t\n79\t- [x] Task 3: Implement patch loading and merging (AC: #2, #3, #4, #5)\n80\t  - [ ] Implement `loadPatch(filePath: string)`: read patch YAML, parse, return `AgentPatch` or null if file missing\n81\t  - [ ] Implement `mergePatch(base: object, patch: AgentPatch)`: deep-merge `overrides` onto base, preserve `prompt_patches` separately\n82\t  - [ ] Deep merge strategy: objects merge recursively, arrays replace (not concatenate), scalars replace\n83\t  - [ ] User patch path: `~/.codeharness/agents/{name}.patch.yaml`\n84\t  - [ ] Project patch path: `.codeharness/agents/{name}.patch.yaml` (relative to cwd)\n85\t  - [ ] Validate merged result against agent schema; throw `AgentResolveError` if invalid\n86\t\n87\t- [ ] Task 4: Implement `resolveAgent()` (AC: #1-5, #8, #9)\n88\t  - [ ] Implement the full resolution chain: load base (embedded or custom) -> merge user patch -> merge project patch -> validate -> return `ResolvedAgent`\n89\t  - [ ] For custom agents (no embedded match, file at project or user level without `extends:`): load directly, validate, return\n90\t  - [ ] For patch files: parse `extends: embedded://name` to identify base\n91\t  - [ ] Silently skip missing patch files (ENOENT), throw on malformed YAML or schema failures\n92\t\n93\t- [ ] Task 5: Implement `compileSubagentDefinition()` (AC: #6, #7)\n94\t  - [ ] Take a `ResolvedAgent` and produce a `SubagentDefinition`\n95\t  - [ ] Build `instructions` string: `\"You are {persona.identity}\\n\\nCommunication style: {persona.communication_style}\\n\\nPrinciples:\\n- {principles joined}\\n\\n{prompt_patches.append if present}\"`\n96\t  - [ ] Set `bare: true` always (per AD2)\n97\t  - [ ] Copy `disallowedTools` from resolved config (empty array if not present)\n98\t  - [ ] Set default `model` (e.g., `\"claude-sonnet-4-20250514\"`) ŌĆö can be overridden by patch\n99\t\n100\t- [ ] Task 6: Write unit tests (AC: #10)\n101\t  - [ ] Create `src/lib/__tests__/agent-resolver.test.ts`\n102\t  - [ ] Test: `resolveAgent(\"dev\")` loads embedded dev.yaml and returns valid ResolvedAgent\n103\t  - [ ] Test: resolveAgent with user patch deep-merges overrides onto embedded base\n104\t  - [ ] Test: resolveAgent with project patch merges on top of user patch\n105\t  - [ ] Test: full 3-layer chain (embedded + user + project) produces correct merged result\n106\t  - [ ] Test: missing user and project patches silently skipped\n107\t  - [ ] Test: malformed patch YAML throws AgentResolveError with file path\n108\t  - [ ] Test: patch that produces schema-invalid result throws AgentResolveError\n109\t  - [ ] Test: compileSubagentDefinition produces correct instructions string\n110\t  - [ ] Test: compileSubagentDefinition preserves disallowedTools for evaluator\n111\t  - [ ] Test: compileSubagentDefinition includes prompt_patches.append in instructions\n112\t  - [ ] Test: custom agent (no extends) loads directly without patch chain\n113\t  - [ ] Test: resolving all 9 embedded agents completes in <200ms\n114\t  - [ ] Test: no regressions in existing test suite\n115\t\n116\t## Dev Notes\n117\t\n118\t### Module Location and Architecture Role\n119\t\n120\tPer architecture-v2 AD1, `agent-resolver` resolves agent config through the patch chain and compiles to SDK inline subagent definition (FR7-12). It lives at `src/lib/agent-resolver.ts` with tests at `src/lib/__tests__/agent-resolver.test.ts`. This module is consumed by `agent-dispatch` (story 4-1) which calls `compileSubagentDefinition()` to get the object passed to the Agent SDK `query()`.\n121\t\n122\t### Resolution Chain (FR11)\n123\t\n124\t```\n125\tembedded://dev (templates/agents/dev.yaml)\n126\t  -> user patch (~/.codeharness/agents/dev.patch.yaml) if exists\n127\t    -> project patch (.codeharness/agents/dev.patch.yaml) if exists\n128\t      -> validate merged result against agent.schema.json\n129\t        -> return ResolvedAgent\n130\t```\n131\t\n132\tMissing patches at any level are silently skipped. Malformed patches (invalid YAML or schema-invalid after merge) fail loudly with `AgentResolveError`.\n133\t\n134\t### Patch File Format (FR9)\n135\t\n136\t```yaml\n137\t# .codeharness/agents/dev.patch.yaml\n138\textends: embedded://dev\n139\toverrides:\n140\t  personality:\n141\t    traits:\n142\t      rigor: 0.9\n143\tprompt_patches:\n144\t  append: |\n145\t    This project uses React + Vite. Run npm run build before\n146\t    considering implementation complete.\n147\t```\n148\t\n149\t- `extends:` ŌĆö identifies the base config. Format: `embedded://name` or `user://name`\n150\t- `overrides:` ŌĆö structured object deep-merged onto the base. Follows agent schema shape.\n151\t- `prompt_patches:` ŌĆö freeform text patches. `append:` adds to end of compiled instructions.\n152\t\n153\t### Deep Merge Strategy\n154\t\n155\t- Objects: merge recursively (base keys preserved, patch keys added or overridden)\n156\t- Arrays: **replace** entirely (patch array replaces base array ŌĆö no concatenation)\n157\t- Scalars: replace (patch value wins)\n158\t\n159\tThis matches the workflow-parser merge strategy implied by the PRD. Arrays replace because concatenation creates unpredictable ordering of principles/tools.\n160\t\n161\t### Subagent Definition Compilation (FR12)\n162\t\n163\tThe `compileSubagentDefinition()` function transforms a `ResolvedAgent` into the shape consumed by the Agent SDK `query()` in story 4-1:\n164\t\n165\t```typescript\n166\tinterface SubagentDefinition {\n167\t  name: string;\n168\t  model: string;          // default: \"claude-sonnet-4-20250514\"\n169\t  instructions: string;   // compiled from persona + prompt_patches\n170\t  disallowedTools: string[];\n171\t  bare: true;             // always true per AD2\n172\t}\n173\t```\n174\t\n175\tThe `instructions` string is compiled from:\n176\t1. `persona.identity` ŌĆö who the agent is\n177\t2. `persona.communication_style` ŌĆö how it talks\n178\t3. `persona.principles` ŌĆö behavioral rules (bulleted)\n179\t4. `prompt_patches.append` ŌĆö additional project-specific instructions (if present from patches)\n180\t\n181\t### Config Resolution Caching (AD4)\n182\t\n183\tThis story implements the resolution function. Caching (resolve once at engine startup) is the responsibility of `workflow-engine` (story 5-1) which will call `resolveAgent()` for all referenced agents and cache the results. This module does NOT implement caching internally ŌĆö it resolves fresh each call.\n184\t\n185\t### Error Handling\n186\t\n187\t| Failure | Response |\n188\t|---------|----------|\n189\t| Missing embedded agent file | `AgentResolveError` (fatal) |\n190\t| Missing user/project patch | Silently skip |\n191\t| Malformed patch YAML | `AgentResolveError` with parse details |\n192\t| Schema-invalid after merge | `AgentResolveError` with validation errors |\n193\t| Custom agent not found | `AgentResolveError` (fatal) |\n194\t\n195\t### What This Story Does NOT Do\n196\t\n197\t- Does NOT implement config caching (that's workflow-engine, story 5-1)\n198\t- Does NOT call the Agent SDK (that's agent-dispatch, story 4-1)\n199\t- Does NOT create or modify any agent YAML files (those were story 3-2)\n200\t- Does NOT modify agent.schema.json (that was story 3-1)\n201\t- Does NOT wire into the validate command (future integration)\n202\t- Does NOT handle `extends: user://name` resolution for project patches extending user agents ŌĆö that is a valid pattern but can be deferred; this story handles `extends: embedded://name` only\n203\t\n204\t### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n205\t\n206\t- **Do NOT write resolved configs to disk** ŌĆö memory-only per architecture AD4\n207\t- **Do NOT cache internally** ŌĆö caching is the engine's responsibility\n208\t- **Do NOT concatenate arrays on merge** ŌĆö arrays replace entirely\n209\t- **Do NOT create a separate Ajv instance** ŌĆö reuse `validateAgentSchema()` from `schema-validate.ts`\n210\t- **Do NOT use `child_process` or shell commands** ŌĆö pure TypeScript file I/O\n211\t- **Do NOT modify embedded templates** ŌĆö they are read-only (NFR12)\n212\t- **Do NOT add `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` as a dependency** ŌĆö that's story 4-1. SubagentDefinition is a plain object interface in this module.\n213\t\n214\t### Dependencies from Previous Stories\n215\t\n216\t- **Story 3-1** created `src/schemas/agent.schema.json` and `validateAgentSchema()` in `src/lib/schema-validate.ts` ŌĆö used for validation\n217\t- **Story 3-2** created 9 agent YAML files in `templates/agents/` ŌĆö the embedded base configs this module loads\n218\t- **Story 2-2** established `workflow-parser.ts` module pattern ŌĆö follow the same structure (single file, typed interfaces, custom error class, exported functions)\n219\t\n220\t### Existing Test Patterns\n221\t\n222\tFollow the pattern in existing tests:\n223\t- Tests are co-located in `src/lib/__tests__/`\n224\t- Use vitest (`describe`, `it`, `expect`)\n225\t- Use `fs.readFileSync` and `yaml.parse` (from the `yaml` package already in dependencies) to load YAML files\n226\t- Use `validateAgentSchema()` from `src/lib/schema-validate.ts` for validation\n227\t- Use `path.resolve(__dirname, '../../templates/agents/')` to locate embedded templates (same pattern as workflow-parser locating schemas)\n228\t- For testing patch files: use `os.tmpdir()` + `fs.mkdtempSync` to create temp directories simulating user/project config locations, or mock `fs.readFileSync` with vitest `vi.mock`\n229\t- Use `vi.spyOn` to mock `os.homedir()` and `process.cwd()` for controlling patch lookup paths\n230\t\n231\t### Git Intelligence\n232\t\n233\tRecent commits follow `feat: story X-Y-slug -- description`. The codebase uses TypeScript with ESM (`\"type\": \"module\"`), vitest for testing, and tsup for building. Story 3-2 (most recent) added 9 agent templates and 85 tests. All modules are single files in `src/lib/` with co-located tests in `__tests__/`.\n234\t\n235\t### Project Structure Notes\n236\t\n237\t- New file: `src/lib/agent-resolver.ts` ŌĆö the agent resolver module\n238\t- New test file: `src/lib/__tests__/agent-resolver.test.ts`\n239\t- No changes to any existing source files\n240\t- No changes to `package.json` (no new dependencies needed ŌĆö uses existing `yaml` and `ajv` packages)\n241\t\n242\t### References\n243\t\n244\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 3.3: Agent Resolver Module]\n245\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD1: Module Boundaries ŌĆö agent-resolver]\n246\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD4: Config Resolution Caching]\n247\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Implementation Patterns ŌĆö Error Handling Patterns]\n248\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Implementation Patterns ŌĆö Structure Patterns]\n249\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#FR7-FR12 ŌĆö Agent Configuration FRs]\n250\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#FR9 ŌĆö patch extends/overrides/prompt_patches]\n251\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#Journey 3 ŌĆö Agent & Workflow Customization]\n252\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#NFR2 ŌĆö Agent config resolution <200ms]\n253\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#NFR12 ŌĆö BMAD agent configs read-only]\n254\t- [Source: src/schemas/agent.schema.json ŌĆö schema for validation]\n255\t- [Source: src/lib/schema-validate.ts ŌĆö validateAgentSchema() function]\n256\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-parser.ts ŌĆö module pattern to follow]\n257\t- [Source: templates/agents/*.yaml ŌĆö embedded agent configs to resolve]\n258\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/3-1-agent-config-json-schema.md ŌĆö predecessor story]\n259\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/3-2-embedded-agent-templates.md ŌĆö predecessor story]\n260\t\n261\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n262\t## Verification Requirements\n263\t\n264\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/3-3-agent-resolver-module-proof.md)\n265\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n266\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n267\t\n268\t## Documentation Requirements\n269\t\n270\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n271\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/3-3-agent-resolver-module.md\n272\t\n273\t## Testing Requirements\n274\t\n275\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n276\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n277\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n278\t\n279\t## Dev Agent Record\n280\t\n281\t### Agent Model Used\n282\t\n283\t{{agent_model_name_version}}\n284\t\n285\t### Debug Log References\n286\t\n287\t### Completion Notes List\n288\t\n289\t### File List\n290\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"605a3302-c654-40ea-969b-1ce171500852","uuid":"aa3a055d-0865-4028-9f67-5918cb9266de","timestamp":"2026-04-02T19:08:22.684Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/3-3-agent-resolver-module.md","content":"# Story 3.3: Agent Resolver Module\n\nStatus: review\n\n<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer,\nI want an agent-resolver that resolves configs through the embedded -> user -> project patch chain and compiles the result into a Claude Code inline subagent definition,\nso that customizations overlay cleanly on embedded defaults and agents are ready for SDK dispatch.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. **Given** an embedded agent name like `\"dev\"` and no user or project patches\n   **When** `resolveAgent(\"dev\")` is called\n   **Then** the embedded config from `templates/agents/dev.yaml` is loaded, parsed, validated against `agent.schema.json`, and returned as a `ResolvedAgent` object\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n2. **Given** an embedded agent `\"dev\"` and a user-level patch file at `~/.codeharness/agents/dev.patch.yaml` with `extends: embedded://dev` and `overrides:` that adds `personality.traits.rigor: 0.9`\n   **When** `resolveAgent(\"dev\")` is called\n   **Then** the embedded config is loaded first, the user patch overrides are deep-merged on top, and the resolved config includes both the original embedded fields and the new `personality.traits.rigor: 0.9`\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n3. **Given** an embedded agent `\"dev\"`, a user-level patch, and a project-level patch at `.codeharness/agents/dev.patch.yaml` with `extends: embedded://dev` and `prompt_patches.append` text\n   **When** `resolveAgent(\"dev\")` is called\n   **Then** resolution order is: embedded base -> user patch merged -> project patch merged on top, and the final config includes the `prompt_patches.append` content in a `prompt_patches` field accessible for downstream compilation\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n4. **Given** an embedded agent `\"dev\"` and no patch files exist at user or project level\n   **When** `resolveAgent(\"dev\")` is called\n   **Then** the missing patches are silently skipped (no error, no warning) and the embedded config is returned unchanged\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n5. **Given** a patch file that contains invalid YAML syntax or fails schema validation after merge\n   **When** `resolveAgent()` processes it\n   **Then** a descriptive `AgentResolveError` is thrown with the file path, parse error or validation errors, and the specific problem ŌĆö resolution does NOT silently return a bad config\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n6. **Given** a resolved agent config (after patch chain)\n   **When** `compileSubagentDefinition()` is called\n   **Then** it returns an object with `name` (string), `model` (string, defaulted), `instructions` (string compiled from persona.identity + communication_style + principles + prompt_patches.append), `disallowedTools` (array, from config or empty), and `bare: true`\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n7. **Given** the evaluator agent with `disallowedTools: [\"Edit\", \"Write\"]`\n   **When** compiled to a subagent definition\n   **Then** the `disallowedTools` array is preserved in the compiled output\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n8. **Given** a user creates a fully custom agent file (not a patch) at `.codeharness/agents/my-agent.yaml` with all required fields and no `extends:`\n   **When** `resolveAgent(\"my-agent\")` is called\n   **Then** the custom agent is loaded directly, validated against `agent.schema.json`, and returned without attempting to find an embedded base ŌĆö no patch chain applies\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n9. **Given** `resolveAgent()` is called for all 9 embedded agents sequentially\n   **When** timed\n   **Then** total resolution completes in <200ms (NFR2)\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n10. **Given** unit tests for the agent-resolver module\n    **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n    **Then** tests pass at 80%+ coverage for `src/lib/agent-resolver.ts` covering: embedded load, user patch merge, project patch merge, full 3-layer chain, missing patches skipped, malformed patch errors, subagent compilation with and without disallowedTools, custom agent (no extends), prompt_patches append, and no regressions in existing tests\n    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n## Tasks / Subtasks\n\n- [x] Task 1: Define TypeScript interfaces (AC: #1, #6)\n  - [ ] Define `ResolvedAgent` interface matching the agent schema shape plus optional `prompt_patches` field\n  - [ ] Define `SubagentDefinition` interface with `name`, `model`, `instructions`, `disallowedTools`, `bare`\n  - [ ] Define `AgentResolveError` error class with `filePath` and `errors` properties\n  - [ ] Define `AgentPatch` interface for patch file structure: `extends`, `overrides`, `prompt_patches`\n\n- [x] Task 2: Implement embedded agent loading (AC: #1, #4)\n  - [ ] Create `src/lib/agent-resolver.ts`\n  - [ ] Implement `loadEmbeddedAgent(name: string)`: read from `templates/agents/{name}.yaml`, parse YAML, validate against agent schema, return typed config\n  - [ ] Throw `AgentResolveError` if embedded agent file not found (fatal per architecture error handling)\n  - [ ] Use `path.resolve(__dirname, '../../templates/agents/')` to locate embedded templates (same pattern as story 3-2 tests)\n\n- [x] Task 3: Implement patch loading and merging (AC: #2, #3, #4, #5)\n  - [ ] Implement `loadPatch(filePath: string)`: read patch YAML, parse, return `AgentPatch` or null if file missing\n  - [ ] Implement `mergePatch(base: object, patch: AgentPatch)`: deep-merge `overrides` onto base, preserve `prompt_patches` separately\n  - [ ] Deep merge strategy: objects merge recursively, arrays replace (not concatenate), scalars replace\n  - [ ] User patch path: `~/.codeharness/agents/{name}.patch.yaml`\n  - [ ] Project patch path: `.codeharness/agents/{name}.patch.yaml` (relative to cwd)\n  - [ ] Validate merged result against agent schema; throw `AgentResolveError` if invalid\n\n- [ ] Task 4: Implement `resolveAgent()` (AC: #1-5, #8, #9)\n  - [ ] Implement the full resolution chain: load base (embedded or custom) -> merge user patch -> merge project patch -> validate -> return `ResolvedAgent`\n  - [ ] For custom agents (no embedded match, file at project or user level without `extends:`): load directly, validate, return\n  - [ ] For patch files: parse `extends: embedded://name` to identify base\n  - [ ] Silently skip missing patch files (ENOENT), throw on malformed YAML or schema failures\n\n- [ ] Task 5: Implement `compileSubagentDefinition()` (AC: #6, #7)\n  - [ ] Take a `ResolvedAgent` and produce a `SubagentDefinition`\n  - [ ] Build `instructions` string: `\"You are {persona.identity}\\n\\nCommunication style: {persona.communication_style}\\n\\nPrinciples:\\n- {principles joined}\\n\\n{prompt_patches.append if present}\"`\n  - [ ] Set `bare: true` always (per AD2)\n  - [ ] Copy `disallowedTools` from resolved config (empty array if not present)\n  - [ ] Set default `model` (e.g., `\"claude-sonnet-4-20250514\"`) ŌĆö can be overridden by patch\n\n- [ ] Task 6: Write unit tests (AC: #10)\n  - [ ] Create `src/lib/__tests__/agent-resolver.test.ts`\n  - [ ] Test: `resolveAgent(\"dev\")` loads embedded dev.yaml and returns valid ResolvedAgent\n  - [ ] Test: resolveAgent with user patch deep-merges overrides onto embedded base\n  - [ ] Test: resolveAgent with project patch merges on top of user patch\n  - [ ] Test: full 3-layer chain (embedded + user + project) produces correct merged result\n  - [ ] Test: missing user and project patches silently skipped\n  - [ ] Test: malformed patch YAML throws AgentResolveError with file path\n  - [ ] Test: patch that produces schema-invalid result throws AgentResolveError\n  - [ ] Test: compileSubagentDefinition produces correct instructions string\n  - [ ] Test: compileSubagentDefinition preserves disallowedTools for evaluator\n  - [ ] Test: compileSubagentDefinition includes prompt_patches.append in instructions\n  - [ ] Test: custom agent (no extends) loads directly without patch chain\n  - [ ] Test: resolving all 9 embedded agents completes in <200ms\n  - [ ] Test: no regressions in existing test suite\n\n## Dev Notes\n\n### Module Location and Architecture Role\n\nPer architecture-v2 AD1, `agent-resolver` resolves agent config through the patch chain and compiles to SDK inline subagent definition (FR7-12). It lives at `src/lib/agent-resolver.ts` with tests at `src/lib/__tests__/agent-resolver.test.ts`. This module is consumed by `agent-dispatch` (story 4-1) which calls `compileSubagentDefinition()` to get the object passed to the Agent SDK `query()`.\n\n### Resolution Chain (FR11)\n\n```\nembedded://dev (templates/agents/dev.yaml)\n  -> user patch (~/.codeharness/agents/dev.patch.yaml) if exists\n    -> project patch (.codeharness/agents/dev.patch.yaml) if exists\n      -> validate merged result against agent.schema.json\n        -> return ResolvedAgent\n```\n\nMissing patches at any level are silently skipped. Malformed patches (invalid YAML or schema-invalid after merge) fail loudly with `AgentResolveError`.\n\n### Patch File Format (FR9)\n\n```yaml\n# .codeharness/agents/dev.patch.yaml\nextends: embedded://dev\noverrides:\n  personality:\n    traits:\n      rigor: 0.9\nprompt_patches:\n  append: |\n    This project uses React + Vite. Run npm run build before\n    considering implementation complete.\n```\n\n- `extends:` ŌĆö identifies the base config. Format: `embedded://name` or `user://name`\n- `overrides:` ŌĆö structured object deep-merged onto the base. Follows agent schema shape.\n- `prompt_patches:` ŌĆö freeform text patches. `append:` adds to end of compiled instructions.\n\n### Deep Merge Strategy\n\n- Objects: merge recursively (base keys preserved, patch keys added or overridden)\n- Arrays: **replace** entirely (patch array replaces base array ŌĆö no concatenation)\n- Scalars: replace (patch value wins)\n\nThis matches the workflow-parser merge strategy implied by the PRD. Arrays replace because concatenation creates unpredictable ordering of principles/tools.\n\n### Subagent Definition Compilation (FR12)\n\nThe `compileSubagentDefinition()` function transforms a `ResolvedAgent` into the shape consumed by the Agent SDK `query()` in story 4-1:\n\n```typescript\ninterface SubagentDefinition {\n  name: string;\n  model: string;          // default: \"claude-sonnet-4-20250514\"\n  instructions: string;   // compiled from persona + prompt_patches\n  disallowedTools: string[];\n  bare: true;             // always true per AD2\n}\n```\n\nThe `instructions` string is compiled from:\n1. `persona.identity` ŌĆö who the agent is\n2. `persona.communication_style` ŌĆö how it talks\n3. `persona.principles` ŌĆö behavioral rules (bulleted)\n4. `prompt_patches.append` ŌĆö additional project-specific instructions (if present from patches)\n\n### Config Resolution Caching (AD4)\n\nThis story implements the resolution function. Caching (resolve once at engine startup) is the responsibility of `workflow-engine` (story 5-1) which will call `resolveAgent()` for all referenced agents and cache the results. This module does NOT implement caching internally ŌĆö it resolves fresh each call.\n\n### Error Handling\n\n| Failure | Response |\n|---------|----------|\n| Missing embedded agent file | `AgentResolveError` (fatal) |\n| Missing user/project patch | Silently skip |\n| Malformed patch YAML | `AgentResolveError` with parse details |\n| Schema-invalid after merge | `AgentResolveError` with validation errors |\n| Custom agent not found | `AgentResolveError` (fatal) |\n\n### What This Story Does NOT Do\n\n- Does NOT implement config caching (that's workflow-engine, story 5-1)\n- Does NOT call the Agent SDK (that's agent-dispatch, story 4-1)\n- Does NOT create or modify any agent YAML files (those were story 3-2)\n- Does NOT modify agent.schema.json (that was story 3-1)\n- Does NOT wire into the validate command (future integration)\n- Does NOT handle `extends: user://name` resolution for project patches extending user agents ŌĆö that is a valid pattern but can be deferred; this story handles `extends: embedded://name` only\n\n### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n\n- **Do NOT write resolved configs to disk** ŌĆö memory-only per architecture AD4\n- **Do NOT cache internally** ŌĆö caching is the engine's responsibility\n- **Do NOT concatenate arrays on merge** ŌĆö arrays replace entirely\n- **Do NOT create a separate Ajv instance** ŌĆö reuse `validateAgentSchema()` from `schema-validate.ts`\n- **Do NOT use `child_process` or shell commands** ŌĆö pure TypeScript file I/O\n- **Do NOT modify embedded templates** ŌĆö they are read-only (NFR12)\n- **Do NOT add `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` as a dependency** ŌĆö that's story 4-1. SubagentDefinition is a plain object interface in this module.\n\n### Dependencies from Previous Stories\n\n- **Story 3-1** created `src/schemas/agent.schema.json` and `validateAgentSchema()` in `src/lib/schema-validate.ts` ŌĆö used for validation\n- **Story 3-2** created 9 agent YAML files in `templates/agents/` ŌĆö the embedded base configs this module loads\n- **Story 2-2** established `workflow-parser.ts` module pattern ŌĆö follow the same structure (single file, typed interfaces, custom error class, exported functions)\n\n### Existing Test Patterns\n\nFollow the pattern in existing tests:\n- Tests are co-located in `src/lib/__tests__/`\n- Use vitest (`describe`, `it`, `expect`)\n- Use `fs.readFileSync` and `yaml.parse` (from the `yaml` package already in dependencies) to load YAML files\n- Use `validateAgentSchema()` from `src/lib/schema-validate.ts` for validation\n- Use `path.resolve(__dirname, '../../templates/agents/')` to locate embedded templates (same pattern as workflow-parser locating schemas)\n- For testing patch files: use `os.tmpdir()` + `fs.mkdtempSync` to create temp directories simulating user/project config locations, or mock `fs.readFileSync` with vitest `vi.mock`\n- Use `vi.spyOn` to mock `os.homedir()` and `process.cwd()` for controlling patch lookup paths\n\n### Git Intelligence\n\nRecent commits follow `feat: story X-Y-slug -- description`. The codebase uses TypeScript with ESM (`\"type\": \"module\"`), vitest for testing, and tsup for building. Story 3-2 (most recent) added 9 agent templates and 85 tests. All modules are single files in `src/lib/` with co-located tests in `__tests__/`.\n\n### Project Structure Notes\n\n- New file: `src/lib/agent-resolver.ts` ŌĆö the agent resolver module\n- New test file: `src/lib/__tests__/agent-resolver.test.ts`\n- No changes to any existing source files\n- No changes to `package.json` (no new dependencies needed ŌĆö uses existing `yaml` and `ajv` packages)\n\n### References\n\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 3.3: Agent Resolver Module]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD1: Module Boundaries ŌĆö agent-resolver]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD4: Config Resolution Caching]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Implementation Patterns ŌĆö Error Handling Patterns]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Implementation Patterns ŌĆö Structure Patterns]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#FR7-FR12 ŌĆö Agent Configuration FRs]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#FR9 ŌĆö patch extends/overrides/prompt_patches]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#Journey 3 ŌĆö Agent & Workflow Customization]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#NFR2 ŌĆö Agent config resolution <200ms]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#NFR12 ŌĆö BMAD agent configs read-only]\n- [Source: src/schemas/agent.schema.json ŌĆö schema for validation]\n- [Source: src/lib/schema-validate.ts ŌĆö validateAgentSchema() function]\n- [Source: src/lib/workflow-parser.ts ŌĆö module pattern to follow]\n- [Source: templates/agents/*.yaml ŌĆö embedded agent configs to resolve]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/3-1-agent-config-json-schema.md ŌĆö predecessor story]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/3-2-embedded-agent-templates.md ŌĆö predecessor story]\n\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n## Verification Requirements\n\n- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/3-3-agent-resolver-module-proof.md)\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n\n## Documentation Requirements\n\n- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/3-3-agent-resolver-module.md\n\n## Testing Requirements\n\n- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n\n## Dev Agent Record\n\n### Agent Model Used\n\n{{agent_model_name_version}}\n\n### Debug Log References\n\n### Completion Notes List\n\n### File List\n","numLines":290,"startLine":1,"totalLines":290}}}
