{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RPJXyu9D3EThP26t2M9i1U","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Status is already `review`. Done.\n\n---\n\n**Summary of work completed:**\n\n1. **Verified existing implementation** ŌĆö Tasks 1-5 (`resolveAgent`, `compileSubagentDefinition`, interfaces, embedded loading, patch merging) were already fully implemented in `src/lib/agent-resolver.ts`\n2. **Fixed 2 TypeScript errors** ŌĆö Type casts from `Record<string, unknown>` to `ResolvedAgent` at lines 258 and 297 needed `as unknown as ResolvedAgent` double-cast\n3. **Added 3 edge case tests** to `src/lib/__tests__/agent-resolver.test.ts`:\n   - Scalar YAML patch (not an object) throws `AgentResolveError`\n   - Unreadable file handling\n   - Error constructor shape for schema validation failure\n4. **All tests pass**: 44 agent-resolver tests, 3801 total tests across 150 files, zero failures\n5. **Coverage**: 93.81% statements, 94.62% lines for `agent-resolver.ts`\n6. **Story marked for review** with all 6 tasks checked off\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Uncovered branches (lines 135-136, 145-149)**: These are error paths inside `loadEmbeddedAgent` for YAML parse errors and schema validation failures on embedded templates. Since embedded templates are read-only shipped files that are always valid, these branches are effectively dead code. Testing them would require module-level mocking of `validateAgentSchema` or corrupting template files on disk, which is fragile. Acceptable at 93.81% coverage.\n- **Type cast pattern**: The `as unknown as ResolvedAgent` double-cast is a code smell ŌĆö it bypasses type safety. A runtime type narrowing function (type guard) would be cleaner but would duplicate the schema validation logic. This is a known trade-off in the codebase pattern.\n- **Pre-existing TS errors**: `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` has 2 unrelated TypeScript errors (lines 188, 200) that predate this work.\n\n## Token Report\n