{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TfX7ZQpGDbV1a3EhZ1z5Ve","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"150 test files, 3806 tests, all passing. Zero regressions. Test count went from 3801 to 3806 (5 new tests).\n\n---\n\n**Review Complete.**\n\n**Story:** 3-3-agent-resolver-module\n**Story Status:** verifying\n**Issues Found:** 3 HIGH, 3 MEDIUM, 2 LOW\n**Issues Fixed:** 3 HIGH, 2 MEDIUM\n**Tests:** 150 files, 3806 tests, 0 failures (was 3801)\n**Coverage:** 96.61% overall, agent-resolver.ts at 94.05% stmts / 83.82% branches / 94.84% lines\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/agent-resolver.ts` ŌĆö added name validation (path traversal prevention), fixed custom agent prompt_patches stripping, fixed return logic mutation\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/agent-resolver.test.ts` ŌĆö added 5 new tests (name validation, custom agent with prompt_patches, error shape coverage)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/3-3-agent-resolver-module.md` ŌĆö status changed to `verifying`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- **HIGH** ŌĆö Path traversal vulnerability: `resolveAgent()` and `loadEmbeddedAgent()` accepted arbitrary strings as agent names, allowing `../../../etc/passwd` style inputs to read arbitrary files. Fixed by adding `validateName()` with regex `^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+$`.\n- **HIGH** ŌĆö `prompt_patches` not stripped during custom agent schema validation: Custom agents with `prompt_patches` would fail `additionalProperties: false` validation, while patched agents had this stripping logic. Fixed by adding the same strip-and-reattach pattern.\n- **HIGH** ŌĆö Mutation + redundant spread in return path: Lines 293-297 mutated `forValidation` (a `const`) then spread it again. While functionally harmless, this was confusing and fragile. Fixed by removing the mutation and using a single conditional spread.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- `loadPatch()` is used to load full custom agent files (not just patches), which is a semantic mismatch. The function returns `AgentPatch` type but the caller immediately casts it to `Record<string, unknown>`. A dedicated `loadCustomAgent()` function would be cleaner.\n- Custom agent at project/user level with same name as an embedded agent (e.g., `dev.yaml`) silently shadows the entire embedded + patch chain. This is by design per AC #8 but could surprise users who have both a custom `dev.yaml` AND `dev.patch.yaml`.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- Lines 153-154, 163-167 in `agent-resolver.ts` (YAML parse error and schema validation failure paths for embedded agents) are untested at runtime. These are defensive branches for corrupted template files. Testing requires `vi.mock('node:fs')` at module level which would require a separate test file. Branch coverage is 83.82%, above the 80% floor.\n- No integration test for the full resolution chain with real filesystem (user home + project dir). All tests use temp dirs and mocked `os.homedir()`.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None significant. Module follows established patterns (single file, typed interfaces, custom error class, exported functions).\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 19\n- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 7, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1, Write: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): full test suite run (~10 lines shown), coverage with all files (~30 lines), first test run (~6 lines)\n- Files read: 9 unique, 10 total reads (agent-resolver.ts read 2 times)\n- Redundant operations: The two failed test runs (attempts to mock named fs imports) could have been avoided by recognizing the named import limitation upfront. One extra coverage grep was needed due to empty output from first attempt."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ab6a1b9bc7ba57f55 (use SendMessage wi