olver-module-proof.md`\n\n**Step 7:** `npx codeharness verify --story 3-3-agent-resolver-module` reports FAIL on two meta-gates: coverage_met (likely checking 100% target from the story verification patch, not the AC's 80%) and AGENTS.md staleness. These are harness-level doc/coverage gates, not AC failures.\n\n**Step 8:** ALL_PASS (10/10 ACs)\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Problems encountered:** `codeharness verify` command fails on two precondition gates: `coverage_met` is false (the harness patch section sets 100% target, while the AC specifies 80% ŌĆö the 94.05% actual coverage passes AC10 but fails the harness 100% gate) and `AGENTS.md` is stale for `src/lib` (missing agent-resolver.ts documentation entry). These are meta-verification gates, not AC failures.\n- **Workarounds applied:** None. Reported the verify command failure as-is without modifying AGENTS.md or coverage thresholds per the instruction not to modify files beyond the proof document.\n- **Verification gaps:** The BATS integration tests (ralph scripts) all fail with exit code 127 (command not found) ŌĆö these are pre-existing failures unrelated to story 3-3. Coverage branch percentage is 83.82%, which is adequate but leaves some defensive error paths uncovered (corrupted embedded templates).\n- **Observations:** The 49 agent-resolver tests are well-structured with explicit AC references in test names, making verification straightforward. All tests run in ~170ms total.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 12\n- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 1, Write: 1, Edit: 0, Grep: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npm test` (~80 lines), `npx vitest run --reporter=verbose` (~80 lines), `npx vitest run --coverage` (~60 lines)\n- Files read: 1 unique, 1 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None significant. Ran vitest twice for agent-resolver (once plain, once verbose) but needed both for counts and test names."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a5c9399af0d1aefff (use SendMessage with to: 'a5c9399af0d