{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CoJtYLfFwns9uVCTB77o7B","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"605a3302-c654-40ea-969b-1ce171500852","uuid":"4c892dd3-7d18-4861-9035-3556ba8a29fb","timestamp":"2026-04-02T19:21:19.294Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"- Redundant operations: Two failed test runs attempting to mock named fs imports could have been avoided","newString":"- Redundant operations: Two failed test runs attempting to mock named fs imports could have been avoided\n\n### 3-3-agent-resolver-module ŌĆö verification (2026-04-02T23:30)\n\n- **Meta-gate failures:** `codeharness verify` flags coverage_met (100% target in story patch vs 94.05% actual ŌĆö AC specifies 80%) and AGENTS.md staleness. These are harness-level gates, not AC failures.\n- **Pre-existing BATS failures:** Integration tests fail with exit 127 (command not found) ŌĆö unrelated to story 3-3.\n- **Branch coverage:** 83.82% ŌĆö defensive error paths for corrupted embedded templates are untested.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 12\n- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 1, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: npm test (~80 lines), vitest verbose (~80 lines), vitest coverage (~60 lines)\n- Files read: 1 unique, 1 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None significant","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log ŌĆö 2026-04-02 (Session 8)\n\n### 3-3-agent-resolver-module ŌĆö create-story (2026-04-02T19:55)\n\n**Problems:** Workflow references `workflow.md` but actual file is `workflow.yaml` + `instructions.xml`. Used both to reconstruct full instructions.\n**Workarounds:** None significant. `SubagentDefinition` defined as plain TS interface since SDK not yet a dependency (story 4-1 adds it).\n**Risks:** AC #9 (<200ms perf) may be flaky on slow CI. Deep merge \"arrays replace\" strategy inferred not confirmed.\n**Observations:** All 10 ACs test-provable. Pure data transformation module.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 19\n- By tool: Bash: 4, Read: 12, Grep: 3, Glob: 6, Write: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: git diff --stat (~17 lines), git log --oneline (~10 lines), ls templates/agents/ (~9 lines)\n- Files read: 13 unique, 13 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None\n\n### 3-3-agent-resolver-module ŌĆö dev-story (2026-04-02T23:10)\n\n- **Uncovered branches (lines 135-136, 145-149)**: Error paths inside `loadEmbeddedAgent` for YAML parse errors and schema validation failures on embedded templates. Since embedded templates are read-only shipped files, these branches are effectively dead code. Acceptable at 93.81% coverage.\n- **Type cast pattern**: `as unknown as ResolvedAgent` double-cast bypasses type safety. A runtime type guard would be cleaner but duplicates schema validation logic. Known trade-off.\n- **Pre-existing TS errors**: `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` has 2 unrelated TypeScript errors (lines 188, 200) predating this work.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 15\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 4, Edit: 4, Grep: 0, Write: 0, other: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs: coverage report (~140 lines), full test suite (~15 lines), tsc errors (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 3 unique, 4 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 3-3-agent-resolver-module ŌĆö code-review (2026-04-02T23:18)\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- **HIGH** ŌĆö Path traversal vulnerability: `resolveAgent()` accepted arbitrary strings, allowing `../../../etc/passwd` style inputs. Fixed with `validateName()` regex.\n- **HIGH** ŌĆö `prompt_patches` not stripped during custom agent schema validation. Fixed.\n- **HIGH** ŌĆö Mutation + redundant spread in return path. Fixed.\n\n**Code quality issues NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- `loadPatch()` used for full custom agent files ŌĆö semantic mismatch\n- Custom agent silently shadows embedded + patch chain (by design per AC #8)\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- Lines 153-154, 163-167 (embedded template error paths) untested ŌĆö defensive branches for corrupted templates\n- No integration test with real filesystem user home + project dir\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 19\n- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 7, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1, Write: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs: full test suite (~10 lines), coverage (~30 lines), first test run (~6 lines)\n- Files read: 9 unique, 10 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Two failed test runs attempting to mock named fs imports could have been avoided\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":48,"oldLines":3,"newStart":48,"newLines":16,"lines":[" - Largest Bash outputs: full test suite (~10 lines), coverage (~30 lines), first test run (~6 lines)"," - Files read: 9 unique, 10 total reads"," - Redundant operations: Two failed test runs attempting to mock named fs imports could have been avoided","+","+### 3-3-agent-resolver-module ŌĆö verification (2026-04-02T23:30)","+","+- **Meta-gate failures:** `codeharness verify` flags coverage_met (100% target in story patch vs 94.05% actual ŌĆö AC specifies 80%) and AGENTS.md staleness. These are harness-level gates, not AC failures.","+- **Pre-existing BATS failures:** Integration tests fail with exit 127 (command not found) ŌĆö unrelated to story 3-3.","+- **Branch coverage:** 83.82% ŌĆö defensive error paths for corrupted embedded templates are untested.","+","+## Token Report","+- Total tool calls: 12","+- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 1, Write: 1","+- Largest Bash outputs: npm test (~80 lines), vitest verbose (~80 lines), vitest coverage (~60 lines)","+- Files read: 1 unique, 1 total reads","+- Redundant operations: None significant"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
