{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0187uCs7pu7VRv91PrjYLDdy","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Session Issues Log ŌĆö 2026-04-02 (Session 8)\n2\t\n3\t### 3-3-agent-resolver-module ŌĆö create-story (2026-04-02T19:55)\n4\t\n5\t**Problems:** Workflow references `workflow.md` but actual file is `workflow.yaml` + `instructions.xml`. Used both to reconstruct full instructions.\n6\t**Workarounds:** None significant. `SubagentDefinition` defined as plain TS interface since SDK not yet a dependency (story 4-1 adds it).\n7\t**Risks:** AC #9 (<200ms perf) may be flaky on slow CI. Deep merge \"arrays replace\" strategy inferred not confirmed.\n8\t**Observations:** All 10 ACs test-provable. Pure data transformation module.\n9\t\n10\t## Token Report\n11\t- Total tool calls: 19\n12\t- By tool: Bash: 4, Read: 12, Grep: 3, Glob: 6, Write: 1, Skill: 1\n13\t- Largest Bash outputs: git diff --stat (~17 lines), git log --oneline (~10 lines), ls templates/agents/ (~9 lines)\n14\t- Files read: 13 unique, 13 total reads\n15\t- Redundant operations: None\n16\t\n17\t### 3-3-agent-resolver-module ŌĆö dev-story (2026-04-02T23:10)\n18\t\n19\t- **Uncovered branches (lines 135-136, 145-149)**: Error paths inside `loadEmbeddedAgent` for YAML parse errors and schema validation failures on embedded templates. Since embedded templates are read-only shipped files, these branches are effectively dead code. Acceptable at 93.81% coverage.\n20\t- **Type cast pattern**: `as unknown as ResolvedAgent` double-cast bypasses type safety. A runtime type guard would be cleaner but duplicates schema validation logic. Known trade-off.\n21\t- **Pre-existing TS errors**: `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` has 2 unrelated TypeScript errors (lines 188, 200) predating this work.\n22\t\n23\t## Token Report\n24\t- Total tool calls: 15\n25\t- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 4, Edit: 4, Grep: 0, Write: 0, other: 0\n26\t- Largest Bash outputs: coverage report (~140 lines), full test suite (~15 lines), tsc errors (~5 lines)\n27\t- Files read: 3 unique, 4 total reads\n28\t- Redundant operations: none\n29\t\n30\t### 3-3-agent-resolver-module ŌĆö code-review (2026-04-02T23:18)\n31\t\n32\t**Bugs found and fixed:**\n33\t- **HIGH** ŌĆö Path traversal vulnerability: `resolveAgent()` accepted arbitrary strings, allowing `../../../etc/passwd` style inputs. Fixed with `validateName()` regex.\n34\t- **HIGH** ŌĆö `prompt_patches` not stripped during custom agent schema validation. Fixed.\n35\t- **HIGH** ŌĆö Mutation + redundant spread in return path. Fixed.\n36\t\n37\t**Code quality issues NOT fixed (LOW):**\n38\t- `loadPatch()` used for full custom agent files ŌĆö semantic mismatch\n39\t- Custom agent silently shadows embedded + patch chain (by design per AC #8)\n40\t\n41\t**Coverage gaps:**\n42\t- Lines 153-154, 163-167 (embedded template error paths) untested ŌĆö defensive branches for corrupted templates\n43\t- No integration test with real filesystem user home + project dir\n44\t\n45\t## Token Report\n46\t- Total tool calls: 19\n47\t- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 7, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1, Write: 0\n48\t- Largest Bash outputs: full test suite (~10 lines), coverage (~30 lines), first test run (~6 lines)\n49\t- Files read: 9 unique, 10 total reads\n50\t- Redundant operations: Two failed test runs attempting to mock named fs imports could have been avoided\n51\t\n52\t### 3-3-agent-resolver-module ŌĆö verification (2026-04-02T23:30)\n53\t\n54\t- **Meta-gate failures:** `codeharness verify` flags coverage_met (100% target in story patch vs 94.05% actual ŌĆö AC specifies 80%) and AGENTS.md staleness. These are harness-level gates, not AC failures.\n55\t- **Pre-existing BATS failures:** Integration tests fail with exit 127 (command not found) ŌĆö unrelated to story 3-3.\n56\t- **Branch coverage:** 83.82% ŌĆö defensive error paths for corrupted embedded templates are untested.\n57\t\n58\t## Token Report\n59\t- Total tool calls: 12\n60\t- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 1, Write: 1\n61\t- Largest Bash outputs: npm test (~80 lines), vitest verbose (~80 lines), vitest coverage (~60 lines)\n62\t- Files read: 1 unique, 1 total reads\n63\t- Redundant operations: None significant\n64\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01D1aPv265mgJjX6WrHHertR","session_id":"605a3302-c654-40ea-969b-1ce171500852","uuid":"ba9634f6-3583-48c7-b7b3-6ca3b5e1cd3c","timestamp":"2026-04-02T19:22:35.264Z"}
