{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0139BZAmkgpz5XoPx8acnYTd","type":"tool_result","content":"1940\t| 2 | Document proof document format in verification subagent instructions | HIGH | process | 15 min |\n1941\t| 3 | Add \"run coverage exactly once\" constraint to code-review and verify subagent prompts | MEDIUM | process | 15 min |\n1942\t| 4 | Fix `codeharness stats` to work without session-logs/ directory | MEDIUM | dev | 30 min |\n1943\t| 5 | Use `--reporter=dot` for vitest in subagents to reduce output size | LOW | process | 10 min |\n1944\t| 6 | Batch fix all recurring LOW issues (config.yaml path, YAML quoting, naming) | LOW | dev | 1 hr |\n1945\t| 7 | Continue Epic 3: next story is 3-3-agent-resolver-module | -- | sprint | next session |\n1946\t\n1947\t---\n1948\t\n1949\t**Session 9 verdict:** Productive session ŌĆö 2 stories done, zero retries, 5 MEDIUM bugs caught by review. The main systemic issue is state sync reliability (second occurrence). Cost analysis reveals verification is 44% of spend and the primary optimization target. Redundant coverage runs are a small but consistent waste (~$1.50/story) that should be eliminated with a prompt-level constraint.\n1950\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01D1aPv265mgJjX6WrHHertR","session_id":"605a3302-c654-40ea-969b-1ce171500852","uuid":"07b55c28-27de-43c8-981a-c1c6250a25ba","timestamp":"2026-04-02T19:24:53.969Z"}
